data.enText: the liquid in a plant or tree that carries food to all its parts

data.chText: 槭糖浆是用糖槭树中提取的树液制成的。
data.enText: Maple syrup is made from sap extracted from the sugar maple tree.
a stupid person that you can easily trick, or treat unfairly
to make sth/sb weaker; to destroy sth gradually

data.chText: 火辣辣的太阳烤得我们虚软无力。
data.enText: The hot sun sapped our energy.

data.chText: 连年失败使他逐渐丧失了自信。
data.enText: Years of failure have sapped him of his confidence.

ex.chText: 这些限制可能会损害医疗保健制度。
ex.enText: These limitations may undermine the health care system.

ex.chText: 最近几次丑闻已动摇了支持者对政府的信心。
ex.enText: The supporters' confidence in the government has been undermined by several recent scandals.

ex.chText: 不断的批评已经损害了他的地位。
ex.enText: The constant criticism has undermined her position.

synonyms.bx: 尤指使信心、权威等变弱或失去效力。

ex.chText: 火辣辣的太阳烤得那些马拉松选手虚软无力。
ex.enText: The hot sun sapped the energy of the marathon runners.

ex.chText: 连年竞选失败使他逐渐丧失了自信。
ex.enText: Years of failures in the elections have sapped him of his confidence.

synonyms.bx: 尤指逐渐削弱某人的力量、信心、意志等。

ex.chText: 他这么做是为了削弱经理的地位。
ex.enText: He did it to weaken the manager's position.

ex.chText: 新的证据削弱了对被告的指控力度。
ex.enText: The new evidence has weakened the case against the accused.

ex.chText: 那些孩子因为长期营养不良而身体衰弱。
ex.enText: The children were weakened by lack of essential nutrients for a long time.

ex.chText: 这些政策动摇了潜在购房者的决心。
ex.enText: These policies have weakened the resolve of potential house buyers.

synonyms.bx: 指使某人或某物变得不重要或不强大，或使人身体衰弱，也可指动摇某人的决心。

tr: a piece of metal covered by leather with a flexible handle
a person who lacks good judgment
a watery solution of sugars, salts, and minerals that circulates through the vascular system of a plant

example: We quickly played out our strength

value.def: If something saps your strength or confidence, it gradually weakens or destroys it.

example.ex: I was afraid the sickness had sapped my strength...
example.tran: 我担心患病已让我元气大伤。

example.ex: Analysts say the recession in Japan has sapped investor confidence.
example.tran: 分析家称日本的经济衰退已经打击了投资者的信心。

value.def: Sap is the watery liquid in plants and trees.

example.ex: The leaves, bark and sap are also common ingredients of local herbal remedies.
example.tran: 树叶、树皮和树汁也是当地草药的常用药材。

value.def: If you describe someone as a sap, you think they are foolish.
